@NODE PicBoot "PicBoot v2.6 by Magnus Holmgren"

@{B}PicBoot v2.6@{UB} by Magnus Holmgren
@{FG FILL}*******************************@{FG TEXT}

Have you removed all output in your 2.0+ startup, and only see a
black screen during boot? Wouldn't it be nice to have a picture
instead? A picture that disappeared when the @{B}Workbench@{UB} screen
opened?

If so, @{B}PicBoot@{UB} is certainly a program for you. What it will do
is to read any IFF file containing an ILBM - or GIF - picture,
and show it. As soon as the @{B}Workbench@{UB} screen appears (or you
press any mouse-button), the picture will go away.

   Features:

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} Fast picture unpacking, using highly optimized assembler. The entire
     picture is read into memory and then unpacked. This applies both to
     the IFF and the GIF unpacker.

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} Optional auto-detaching; the picture is loaded as fast as possible,
     with minimal memory fragmentation.

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} A picture can be shown a user-specified time after the @{B}Workbench@{UB} screen
     opens.

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} Extremely flexible argument parser.

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} Random select among any number of pictures, in several different ways.

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} Force a certain display mode for a picture, even if saved with another
     (can be selected on a picture by picture basis).

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} The comment field of a file may be used to specify options.

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} Optional screen centering (horizontally).

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} Optional screen fading (in various forms). Uses the increased palette
     range in AA (24 bits).

   @{FG FILL}*@{FG TEXT} Should work with most "Intuition emulators" for gfx-cards.

@ENDNODE

